### Employment Agreement Template
```markdown
# Employment Agreement

This Employment Agreement ("Agreement") is entered into as of [Date] between:

**Employer**: [Company Name], a [State] [corporation/LLC] ("Company")
**Employee**: [Employee Name] ("Employee")

## 1. Position and Duties

### 1.1 Position
Employee is hired as [Job Title], reporting to [Manager Title]. Employee will perform duties consistent with this position and as assigned by the Company.

### 1.2 Full-Time Employment
Employee agrees to devote full business time and efforts to Company business. Employee may not engage in other employment or business activities that conflict with Company duties without written approval.

### 1.3 Work Location
Employee's primary work location will be [Location]. [Remote work provisions if applicable.]

## 2. Compensation

### 2.1 Base Salary
Company will pay Employee a base salary of $[Amount] per year, payable [bi-weekly/semi-monthly] in accordance with Company's payroll practices.

### 2.2 Bonus
Employee may be eligible for a discretionary bonus of up to [X]% of base salary, based on individual and company performance. Bonus eligibility and amounts are determined by Company in its sole discretion.

### 2.3 Equity [If Applicable]
Subject to Board approval, Employee will be granted [X] stock options/RSUs under the Company's Equity Incentive Plan. Vesting and other terms will be set forth in a separate grant agreement.

## 3. Benefits

### 3.1 Standard Benefits
Employee is eligible to participate in Company benefit programs, subject to plan terms and eligibility requirements.

### 3.2 Paid Time Off
Employee will accrue [X] days of PTO per year, in accordance with Company policy.

### 3.3 Expense Reimbursement
Company will reimburse Employee for reasonable business expenses incurred in performing job duties, subject to Company policy and documentation requirements.

## 4. At-Will Employment

Employment with Company is "at-will." Either party may terminate the employment relationship at any time, with or without cause or advance notice. Nothing in this Agreement creates a contract for any specific duration of employment.

## 5. Confidentiality

### 5.1 Confidential Information
Employee acknowledges that during employment, Employee will have access to Confidential Information, including but not limited to: trade secrets, customer information, business strategies, financial information, and technical data.

### 5.2 Non-Disclosure
Employee agrees not to disclose, use, or permit the use of any Confidential Information, except as required in performing job duties, both during and after employment.

### 5.3 Return of Materials
Upon termination, Employee will immediately return all Company property and Confidential Information.

## 6. Intellectual Property

### 6.1 Work Product Assignment
Employee agrees that all inventions, discoveries, developments, and works created during employment that relate to Company business are "work made for hire" and belong exclusively to Company.

### 6.2 Moral Rights Waiver
To the extent permitted by law, Employee waives all moral rights in any work product.

### 6.3 Cooperation
Employee agrees to execute any documents and take any actions necessary to perfect Company's ownership of work product.

## 7. Restrictive Covenants [Include based on jurisdiction]

### 7.1 Non-Competition [If enforceable in jurisdiction]
During employment and for [X] months after termination, Employee will not engage in Competitive Activity within [Geographic Area].

### 7.2 Non-Solicitation of Employees
For [X] months after termination, Employee will not solicit or hire any Company employee.

### 7.3 Non-Solicitation of Customers
For [X] months after termination, Employee will not solicit Company customers with whom Employee had material contact.

## 8. Termination

### 8.1 Voluntary Resignation
Employee agrees to provide [X] weeks written notice of resignation when practicable.

### 8.2 Company Termination
Company may terminate employment at any time, with or without cause. [Severance provisions if applicable.]

### 8.3 Post-Termination Obligations
Sections 5, 6, and 7 survive termination of employment.

## 9. General Provisions

### 9.1 Entire Agreement
This Agreement, together with any offer letter and equity agreements, constitutes the entire agreement between the parties regarding employment.

### 9.2 Amendments
This Agreement may only be amended in writing signed by both parties.

### 9.3 Governing Law
This Agreement is governed by the laws of [State].

### 9.4 Severability
If any provision is unenforceable, the remaining provisions continue in effect.

---

**COMPANY**: [Company Name]

By: _________________________ Date: _____________
Name:
Title:

**EMPLOYEE**:

_________________________ Date: _____________
[Employee Name]
```

