### Workplace Investigation Guide
```markdown
# Workplace Investigation Protocol

## When to Investigate
- Harassment or discrimination complaints
- Retaliation allegations
- Policy violations
- Misconduct reports
- Safety concerns
- Theft or fraud allegations
- Workplace violence threats

## Investigation Framework

### Phase 1: Initial Assessment (Day 1-2)

#### 1.1 Receive Complaint
- [ ] Document complaint receipt (date, time, method)
- [ ] Identify complainant and accused
- [ ] Determine nature of allegations
- [ ] Assess urgency and severity

#### 1.2 Initial Decisions
| Decision | Options |
|----------|---------|
| Investigator | Internal HR / External investigator |
| Interim measures | Administrative leave / Separation / None |
| Notification | Legal / Leadership / Insurance |
| Timeline | Standard / Expedited |

#### 1.3 Evidence Preservation
- [ ] Preserve relevant documents
- [ ] Preserve electronic communications
- [ ] Secure physical evidence
- [ ] Issue litigation hold (if needed)

### Phase 2: Planning (Day 2-3)

#### 2.1 Investigation Plan
```
Allegation Summary: [Brief description]

Key Questions to Answer:
1. [Question]
2. [Question]
3. [Question]

Witnesses to Interview:
1. Complainant
2. Accused
3. [Witness names]

Documents to Review:
- [Document list]

Timeline: [Target completion date]
```

#### 2.2 Interview Schedule
| Person | Role | Date | Time | Location |
|--------|------|------|------|----------|
| [Name] | Complainant | | | |
| [Name] | Accused | | | |
| [Name] | Witness | | | |

### Phase 3: Fact-Finding (Days 3-14)

#### 3.1 Interview Protocol
**Opening:**
- Introduce yourself and your role
- Explain purpose of investigation
- Assure no retaliation
- Explain confidentiality expectations
- Ask permission to take notes

**During Interview:**
- Ask open-ended questions
- Let them tell their story
- Follow up for details
- Ask about witnesses and evidence
- Avoid leading questions
- Remain neutral

**Closing:**
- Ask if anything else to share
- Explain next steps
- Remind about confidentiality
- Provide contact information
- Thank them for cooperation

#### 3.2 Interview Notes Template
```
Interview Notes

Date/Time: [Date/Time]
Location: [Location]
Interviewer: [Name]
Interviewee: [Name]
Role: Complainant / Accused / Witness

Summary of Statements:
[Detailed notes of what was said]

Documents/Evidence Provided:
[List any items provided]

Demeanor/Observations:
[Relevant observations]

Follow-up Needed:
[Additional items to investigate]

Interviewer Signature: _____________ Date: _______
```

#### 3.3 Document Review
- [ ] Personnel files
- [ ] Relevant policies
- [ ] Email communications
- [ ] Text messages
- [ ] Calendar entries
- [ ] Access logs
- [ ] Video footage
- [ ] Prior complaints

### Phase 4: Analysis & Conclusion (Days 14-18)

#### 4.1 Credibility Assessment
| Factor | Complainant | Accused | Witnesses |
|--------|-------------|---------|-----------|
| Consistency | | | |
| Corroboration | | | |
| Demeanor | | | |
| Motive to lie | | | |
| Plausibility | | | |

#### 4.2 Findings
For each allegation:
- **Allegation**: [Description]
- **Standard**: Preponderance of evidence (more likely than not)
- **Finding**: Substantiated / Unsubstantiated / Inconclusive
- **Reasoning**: [Explanation of conclusion]

### Phase 5: Reporting (Days 18-21)

#### 5.1 Investigation Report
```
CONFIDENTIAL - ATTORNEY-CLIENT PRIVILEGED [if applicable]

WORKPLACE INVESTIGATION REPORT

Prepared by: [Name]
Date: [Date]

I. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
[Brief overview of complaint, investigation, and findings]

II. ALLEGATIONS
[List each allegation investigated]

III. INVESTIGATION PROCESS
[Describe methodology, interviews, documents reviewed]

IV. RELEVANT POLICIES
[Cite applicable policies]

V. SUMMARY OF EVIDENCE
[Factual summary without conclusions]

VI. CREDIBILITY ASSESSMENT
[Analysis of witness credibility]

VII. FINDINGS
[Conclusions for each allegation]

VIII. RECOMMENDATIONS
[Suggested actions if substantiated]
```

### Phase 6: Resolution (Days 21-28)

#### 6.1 Disciplinary Action (if warranted)
| Finding | Possible Actions |
|---------|-----------------|
| Minor violation | Coaching, verbal warning |
| Moderate violation | Written warning, training |
| Serious violation | Final warning, suspension |
| Severe violation | Termination |

#### 6.2 Communication
- [ ] Inform complainant of outcome
- [ ] Inform accused of outcome
- [ ] Document remedial actions
- [ ] Follow up on implementation

#### 6.3 Prevention Measures
- [ ] Additional training
- [ ] Policy updates
- [ ] Process improvements
- [ ] Monitoring plan
```

